<p>* When the initials <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">[ts]</span> &lt;z&gt;, <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">[tsʰ]</span> &lt;c&gt;, <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">[s]</span> &lt;s&gt;, and <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">[ŋ]</span> &lt;ng&gt;, are followed by a <a href="/wiki/Palatal_approximant" title="Palatal approximant">palatal</a> <a href="/wiki/Medial_(linguistics)" title="Medial (linguistics)">medial</a> <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">[j]</span> &lt;i&gt;, they become <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">[tɕ]</span> &lt;j&gt;, <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">[tɕʰ]</span> &lt;q&gt;, <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">[ɕ]</span> &lt;x&gt;, and <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">[ɲ]</span> &lt;ng&gt;, respectively.</p>
<h4><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Hakka_Chinese&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8" title="Edit section: Rimes">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Rimes">Rimes</span></h4>
<p>Moiyen Hakka has six vowels, <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">[i ɨ ɛ a ə ɔ u]</span>, that are romanised as i, ê, a, e, o and u, respectively. The palatisation medial (<span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">[j]</span>) is represented by i and the labialisation medial (<span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">[w]</span>) is represented as u.</p>
<p>Moreover, Hakka <a href="/wiki/Syllable_rime" title="Syllable rime">rimes</a> exhibits the final consonants found in Middle Chinese, namely <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">[m, n, ŋ, p, t, k]</span> which are romanised as m, n, ng, b, d, and g respectively in the official Moiyen romanisation.</p>
